Armed bandits on Friday night invaded Batati town in Lavun local government area of Niger state leaving several people injured. Eyewitness account stated that the bandits arrived the community in a white Hilux vehicle and perform congregational Ishai prayers at about 8pm with the members of the community. It was learnt that after the prayers, the bandits began firing into the air causing people to run and hide for safety. The bandits were said to be more than 20 and operated in some shops along the major road to Mokwa carting away money, laptops, handsets and other valuables. Eyewitnesses also disclosed that after operating for several hours, the bandits took to the forest of Fazhi and Kutigi as they went away.